"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The use of `shift(-1)` in the lambda function within `apply` can lead to issues because it may not handle the last row of each group correctly. The resulting Series from `shift(-1)` will have NaN for the last row, which can cause unexpected behavior when performing comparisons.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1).fillna(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1).fillna(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\"\n}"